description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an established staff nurse to join our friendly professional team in elective orthopaedics. The post is for 35.5 hours to be worked over 4 days or 3 nights when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward M2 is a 20 bed ring fenced elective orthopaedic ward based on the Clatterbridge site. All of our patients are admitted directly to the ward and although primarily we care for patients having arthroplasty surgery we also have patients admitted for upper and lower limb surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally the successful candidate will have orthopaedic experience and a willingness to support and share your knowledge with students and junior members of the team. Knowledge of our computer system cerna is an advantage but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;M2 orthopaedic is a nurse led discharge ward. There is a team of ward based physiotherapists and occupational therapists whom we work closely with on a daily basis we are also supported by an advanced nurse practioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the ward is an elective ward we do have quieter periods during this time it is expected that staff will move to Arrowe Park to support our colleagues. A professional approach to this is expected and required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SR Helen Donaldson or SR Alison Roberts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Direct dial: 0151 482 7758&lt;/p&gt;
